rComments: This professor is one of the best English teachers Ive had. It does take a lot of reading in order to understand the material but when he goes over it and explains it makes it so much easier. The assignments are easy and straightforward and honestly if you watch the lectures you cant fail this course. Would definitely take it again!!
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Prof. Wilson genuinely cares about his students. Although his lectures could get long and boring at times, it is totally worth taking his class. 30% of your mark is an easy 100 for discussion posts and then there is one research essay. At the end of the semester, I asked the prof. for more assistance and he helped me get the grade I wanted.
if you're looking for a gpa booster, take this. professor wilson is super nice and a pretty fair grader, 30% of our grade was for easy discussion posts.

Great class and prof. I loved the subject and hes real chill. He explains everything in his lectures so just be competent. Two essays and two more for final, but standard length, not overbearing. Good text choices too. Just be good at writing ? Plus his brightspace page is a sight to behold, and very useful. Took it for fun and it was.

After looking at the one review that is written here I was apprehensive in taking this class. Thank God I did. This class is one of the easiest things I have ever done. We are required to buy three books, I bought the first one and I sparknotes'd the rest of them and got 80's in everything. You don't need to go to class. This class is a blessing
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback']
